The '''Khoz'zhak''' was an ancient piece of [[Gree (species)/Legends|Gree]] technology whose purpose remained unknown. By the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial period]], it was a guarded by a tribe of feral [[Gree (species)/Legends|Gree]] living deep in the wilderness of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Asation]] and also jealously pursued by Gree artifact-keepers from [[Te Hasa/Legends|Te Hasa]].

It was discovered among ancient ruins in the jungles of Asation by [[Henrietya Antilles|Corellia Antilles]]' survey group, after which point they were pursued by jungle-dwelling Gree and various beasts. Antilles was forced to hide the device in a structure two days' travel out from [[Satikan]], and made her way back to the city.<ref name=":0">[[The Gree Enclave|''The Gree Enclave'']], [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 8]].</ref> Most members of the expedition lost their lives.<ref>[[From the Files of Corellia Antilles|''From the Files of Corellia Antilles'']], [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 14]].</ref> A group of Gree artifact-keepers from Te Hasa obsessed with retrieving the Khoz'zhak arrived on Asation to stop her, but she narrowly escaped them and hired a small team of visiting adventurers to retrieve the artifact while she went into hiding. Though they were successful, the Te Hasan Gree caught up with them and demanded an exchange, paying a large number of [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] and one Gree device of lesser import for the Khoz'zhak.<ref name=":0" />

